SIMPLE: embolic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embolic
<hw>Em*bol"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to throw
in. See <er>Embolism</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Embolismic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to an embolism;
produced by an embolism; <as>as, an <ex>embolic</ex>
abscess</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Pushing or growing in; -- said of
a kind of invagination. See under <er>Invagination</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embolism</ent>⟦br⟧
